'''Drain life''' is a monster attack [[damage type]] that may reduce the [[experience level]] of the defender.

== Description ==

If a drain life attack hits and passes through [[magic cancellation]], then it has a {{frac|1|3}} chance of taking effect.

It may be prevented by [[drain resistance]], [[magic cancellation]], or if the attacker is a [[cancelled]] monster.

=== Versus characters ===

{{main|Experience level#Losing levels}}
The character's experience level is reduced by 1, killing them if their level reaches 0; their [[experience points]] are reduced to the maximum for their new level. Maximum and current [[hit points]] and [[energy]] are reduced by the same amount as they would have been increased had the player gained a level. They cannot be reduced below one hit point and zero energy points.{{refsrc|src/mhitu.c|1195|nethack=3.6.7}}{{refsrc|src/exper.c|200|nethack=3.6.7}}

=== Versus monsters ===

The monster's level is reduced by 1, killing them if their level reaches 0; their maximum and current hit points are reduced by [[D notation|2d6]]. If their hit points are reduced below 1, they die.{{refsrc|src/mhitm.c|1301|nethack=3.6.7}}

== Monsters with the attack ==

The following monsters have this attack:
* {{white|V}} [[vampire (monster class)|all vampires]]
* {{white|W}} [[wraith (monster class)|all wraith class monsters]]
* {{monsymlink|Demogorgon}}

Additionally, if the [[sysconf#SEDUCE|system configuration option]] SEDUCE is not set, then [[foocubi]] have a drain life attack rather than a seduction attack.

== Internals ==

Drain life is represented by the macro '''AD_DRLI'''.{{refsrc|include/monattk.h|52|nethack=3.6.7}}

== Strategy ==

[[Magic cancellation]] and an extremely good [[armor class]] reduce the chances of an attack hitting and getting through. If you expect to get hit many times, you can equip MC3 items or wield one of the [[drain resistance]] artifacts. 

Most of the time, the hero immediately regains the first lost level from the experience gained by killing the attacker. If you do lose two or more levels at once, you can regain all the levels by quaffing a blessed [[potion of restore ability]], or regain one level by quaffing an uncursed [[potion of restore ability]] or a blessed [[potion of full healing]].

